We were given lower floor and had to deal with construction noise across the street and the on-ramp to the freeway.	The hotel and rooms are gorgeous, and the location is perfect--downtown but on a fairly quiet street.	Our room was quiet and comfortable and had windows that open!	Only negative - we were on the 3rd flr & thought the room could have benefitted from double glazed windows to stop the traffic noise in the morning.	There is quite a bit of outside noise that makes it into the rooms and I was awakened at 06:00 by a dumptruck below my window.